5. Find the value of â€œxâ€ in the equation 2a2 + 2xa + 5x + 10 if (a + x) is one of its factors.
Solution:
Say, f(a) = 2a2 + 2xa + 5x + 10
Since, (a + x) is a factor of 2a2 + 2xa + 5x + 10, f(-x) = 0
So, f(-x) = 2x2 â€“ 2x2 â€“ 5x + 10 = 0
Or, -5x + 10 = 0
Thus, x = 2

